    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow more funding for Ex-Military and Ex-Service personnel suffering with PTSD.",
        "additional_details": "Why should the people who fought so hard for our lives be the ones left to suffer?\r\n\r\nPTSD is marked by clear physical and psychological symptoms.\u00a0It often has symptoms like\u00a0depression, substance abuse, problems of memory and cognition, and other physical and mental health problems. The disorder is also associated with difficulties in social or family life, including occupational instability, marital problems, family discord, and difficulties in parenting.\r\n\r\nREF- https://www.military.com/benefits/veterans-health-care/posttraumatic-stress-disorder-overview.html",
        "background": "It is far too common for our Ex- Service and Ex-Military personnel to be suffering with PTSD. People who suffer from PTSD often suffer from\u00a0nightmares, flashbacks, difficulty sleeping, and feeling emotionally numb. These symptoms can significantly impair a person's daily life.",
